      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>fennel seeds</strong> to the pot and cook for 30 secs or until aromatic (not a big fennel seeds fan? Try using less!)</p><p>Once aromatic, add the <strong>saffron stock</strong>,<strong> bay leaves</strong>,<strong> chopped potato </strong>and <strong>white crab meat</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until the potatoes are cooked through</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
